2.20.20  12:37 pm   if i were to tell you that i have a really hard time recording strictly to a click, without the need for editing rhythms later, but REALLY DESPERATELY desire for my time to be better so i can feel comfortable recording to click and even without, could you offer me any advice on getting better at this over time? is just making more stuff to a click going to help?

      yes, i think that will help. also listening to a lot of music that has been recorded to a click (which is most music). contrary to what you might think, paying closer attention is probably not what gets you there. for this, relaxation definitely is the key, and honestly another thing i've noticed, and this may not be what you want to hear, but what i think also helps is AGE
